    <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><font size="2"><font face="Microsoft Sans Serif" size="2">

<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Rydda`Dar</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Rydda`Dar">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b> 68-68<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font> Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font> Rare_Monster<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font> Halls of Honor<br>









<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font><br>- Hits for up to 2060 per attack.<BR>- PBAE Fear is magic based (-200) and only lasts for six seconds. It also snares the player and lowers their armor class and attack speed.<BR>- Procs 2000 point direct damage spell.<BR>- Rampages<BR>- Disease Slowable(Mitigated)<BR>- Will spawn in the middle of the room immediately after Trydan Faye is killed and will attack.<BR><BR><b>Spawn and Scouting</b><BR><BR>The Rydda`Dar Trial is initiated by Trydan Faye in the near right basement. He can be tracked from about half of the zone, as well. Occasionally there are see invis mobs on the way, so con the mobs in his basement area before running by them. <BR><BR>This trial is a 3 day spawn.<BR><BR><b>What You Need</b><BR><BR>The needs of this trial really vary depending on your gear and luck. This trial could be done by 30 elemental or time geared players if luck was on their side and they get hit with fear early. For pre-elemental guilds you will want to bring 50+. DPS is the king in this fight: the more you have the easier it gets.<BR><BR>You will need at least two good tanks for Rydda`Dar. His DPS is surpassed only by Mithaniel Marr on pre-elemental mobs. You will also need at least 4 good clerics, but the more the better. We did this trial once with a 3 cleric chain, but if you are short on clerics you will need great DPS to make up for it. You will need at least one bard and as many CoD enchanters as you can possibly muster. The more enchanters, the easier the fight.<BR><BR><b>Preparation</b><BR><BR>Players typically meet in the corner to the right hand of the alcove upon entering the trial room. You can either invis or COTH down. There are sometimes see invis mobs on the way down though, so check first. Make sure that any players who get aggro die instead of training the raid.<BR><BR>Before you begin the trial you are going to want to get pets for each CoD enchanter in the raid. DPS is king, and charmed pets are great DPS. The trick here is that you need pets from outside of the trial room. Once the trial is initiated all guards inside of the room despawn. So you should grab your pets from the adjacent rooms. Sentries don't make good pets because they are not snareable. Have one player pull pets in to the trial room one by one. They should then be snared, debuffed and charmed. Enchanters should park their pets away from the corner that the raid is in. This way if charm breaks the pets move away from the raid and towards the enchanter.<BR><BR><b>The Fight</b><BR><BR>This trial is initiated by telling Trydan Faye that you are ready. Once this is done a Custodian of Marr will spawn and attack the player initiating the trial. That player should quickly move to the corner where the raid is. The Custodian himself is an easy kill, but it is very important that before he dies everyone in the raid backs off of him and gets in to the corner except for the main tank and rampage tank. They should finish him off with the help of pets between the corner and the middle of the room. All other warriors should be on standby. It is very likely that the main tank or the ch chain may be feared early in the fight and things can go downhill quickly. So everyone needs to be on their toes.<BR><BR>As soon as the Custodian dies Rydda`Dar will spawn and attack the nearest player. This is why the main tank should be the furthest out. The initial few seconds of this fight are the most dangerous. All songs should be turned off before the Custodian dies. Once the main tank has established aggro and rampage has been set then bards should pump maximum magic resistance and enchanters need to get their pets in the fight as quickly as possible. He is only slowable with disease based slow, and the faster you can get it the better your chances of a clean win.<BR><BR>Rydda Dars DPS is high for a pre-elemental mob. He hits for up to 2060 per attack, is only disease slowable and has a 2000 point proc. You will need at least a four cleric CH chain, a 6 cleric chain is best. Some guilds choose to use two seperate 4 cleric chains if possible in case one of the clerics is feared. We've always just used one chain and it's worked fine, just be sure that clerics use max magic reistance gear and have a bard in their group playing magic resistance.<BR><BR>His fear is magic based and only has a -200 modifier. This means that with decent magic resistance (300+) your going to resist it most of the time. The fear only lasts for six seconds, but those six seconds can be deadly if it is your main tank or cleric chain. Don't forget to assign a bard to both the cleric and tank groups to avoid this. Have another bard playing AE magic resistance to aid those groups without a dedicated bard.<BR><BR>This fight ranges from easy (if the main tank stays up and does not get feared) to the worst form of a sloppy zerg (if main tank or ch chain gets feared too much or dies early). No matter how much experience you have here it can still get sloppy quickly. Because of this DPS is the key. The faster he falls the less chance you have of the wrong person being feared. Drop him quickly.<BR><BR><b>Loot</b><BR><BR>Rydda`Dar drops two items at a time, and ornate counts as a drop. He also has a chance to drop runes and spectral parchments. He only has a 3 loot table + ornate breastplates and in general his loot is subpar for the effort required. The monk/beastlord 1hander is the only good drop. <BR><BR>The real reward here is the flag. All three Halls of Honor Trials + Aerin Dar = Temple of Mithaniel Marr access.<br>

<br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>
<font color=#d2d200>Ornate Plate Breastplate Mold</font><br>
